1. Core Foundations (Completed/In Progress)
Aesthetics: High-contrast Sci-Fi theme (Deep Black/Blue #020205) with Neon Cyan, Purple, and Pink accents.

Background: Custom CircuitBoardBackground with animated "Comet" beams and a subtle X-Grid.

Typography: Orbitron for headers and Rajdhani or Share Tech Mono for data/monospaced text.

The "Glass" Standard: All UI elements use Frosted Glass (backdrop-blur-xl) with "thick" layering (double borders).

2. The Arena (Matchmaking & Lobbies)
Unified Lobby System: One system for both automated "Queues" and player-hosted "Lobbies."

Triple-Tier Layout: 1. Tournament Row: Official events (Neon Red). 2. My Operations: Lobbies you are hosting (Electric Purple). 3. Open Grid: All available joinable games (Neon Cyan).

Guild-Locked Visibility: Players only see lobbies for Discord servers they are actually in.

Sector Keys (Private Lobbies): 4-digit Hex-code passphrases (e.g., A7-F2) for locked sessions.

Match Found "Ready Check": A 10-second countdown overlay with "Accept/Decline" before a match starts.

Map Veto System: A tactical "Ban/Pick" phase for mission locations (e.g., Valorant maps).

3. The Dossier (Player Career)
Public/Private Views: A single profile page that hides sensitive info/controls when viewed by others.

Shared Sectors: Displays mutual Discord servers between you and the player you are viewing.

Recent Operatives: A compact list of the last 5 players you played with, integrated directly into the profile.

Unified Trophy Case: A grid for both Global Achievements (public) and Secret Organization Medals (hidden unless earned).

Reputation Meter: A neon bar fueled by player commendations (e.g., "Good Leader," "Clutch Factor").

Game-Specific Stats: Dedicated data tabs for the "Big 5" (LoL, Valorant, Rocket League, FIFA, CS2).

4. Admin & Systems (The "Command Center")
Floating Admin Hub: A persistent, bobbing red notification bubble visible only to admins, showing pending reports.

Lightweight Inbox: A text-only report system for match approvals.

Discord-Linked Evidence: No image hosting; players upload screenshots to Discord logs, and the site links to those threads for verification.

Official Mode Registry: A master list of "Official" vs. "Community" game modes.

Ghost Lobby Cleanup: Automated "Reaper" script that removes lobbies if the host goes offline or is inactive for 2 hours.

5. Planned / Provisions
Automatic Rank Sync: Pulling Discord roles to update Dossier stats automatically.

Tournament Architect: Admin tools to set Round Robin or Gauntlet bracket styles.

Reputation Decay: Stats slowly dropping during inactivity to encourage consistent play.

Mode Promotion: A way for popular "Community" modes to be upgraded to "Official" status by admins.

